race.comment: MERCURIAL LADY (12) was outdashed last time. That isn't the way to go about it with her. She has run her best races when the tempo has been genuine and that should be the case here. She has left a few nice chances on the table but this is another one and fancy that she can take it. GROUSE MOUNTAIN (10) will be among those sliding forward from out wide. Not at her best last time but she is generally reliable and the fresh run said that she had come back in good order. Jury might be out on that for RIPROAR (5) who only beat a couple home first up for 16 months but it was a bunched finish and 1000m is not his go. He can improve panels second up. EL TERCERO (8) was too good at Moe and this might not take a great deal more winning. LAA DE SHA (1) has been second and first in Flemington jump outs, shaping as though ready to run a big race on return while PRIMAL SPIRIT (3) was able to tough things out and win at Sandown and finds a race lacking for star power in which to follow up.
